PHASE 1.5 — DOCKER CHANGES FOR MODEL PROVIDERS (NEW)

Why this is needed:
  We added a model provider abstraction so the backend can use Ollama (local),
  Anthropic (Claude), or OpenAI (GPT-4o). When using a cloud provider like Claude,
  the Ollama container is unnecessary and wastes 4–8 GB of RAM sitting idle.
  We want to make Ollama optional — only start it when you actually need local models.

What changed in the backend:
  - New config field: MODEL_PROVIDER (values: ollama, anthropic, openai)
  - New config fields: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY (only needed for cloud providers)
  - New files in backend/agent/providers/ — one per LLM provider
  - The backend no longer hardcodes Ollama — it reads MODEL_PROVIDER and uses the right provider

What needs to change in docker-compose.yml:

  1. Add a Docker Compose profile to the ollama service
     This makes Ollama only start when explicitly requested.

     Change the ollama service to include:
       profiles: ["local"]

     Before:
       ollama:
         image: ollama/ollama
         ports:
           - "11434:11434"
         ...

     After:
       ollama:
         image: ollama/ollama
         profiles: ["local"]
         ports:
           - "11434:11434"
         ...

  2. Remove ollama from backend's depends_on
     The backend should start without waiting for Ollama when using a cloud provider.

     Before:
       backend:
         depends_on:
           postgres:
             condition: service_healthy
           ollama:
             condition: service_healthy

     After:
       backend:
         depends_on:
           postgres:
             condition: service_healthy

  3. Usage after the change:

     Using a cloud provider (Claude or GPT-4o):
       - Set MODEL_PROVIDER=anthropic (or openai) in .env
       - Set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-... (or OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...) in .env
       - Run: docker compose up
       - Ollama does NOT start. Saves 4–8 GB of RAM.

     Using Ollama (local model):
       - Set MODEL_PROVIDER=ollama in .env
       - Run: docker compose --profile local up
       - Ollama starts alongside everything else, same as before.

  4. No other Docker changes needed
     - Postgres stays the same
     - Frontend stays the same
     - Backend Dockerfile stays the same (the provider code is already in the backend image)
     - .env already has the new fields documented in .env.example

